{
  "doc_id": "41110",
  "text": "Tsiouris et al [CITATION_1] reported a 75-year-old male with dyspnea and shock due to acute BPVT and obstruction of a mitral valve prosthesis implanted 2 months earlier; he recovered following redo operation and anticoagulation. Hypercoagulable workup was negative, including factor V Leiden, prothrombin gene mutation, protein C/S, antithrombin III, homocysteine levels and antiphospholipid antibodies. He only had erythrocytosis with a hematocrit of 60% 1 month prior to his presentation, which was present on admission with cardiogenic shock, but resolved 1 month postoperatively.",
